headline: Cboe Global Markets (CBOE) Margin Gains Reinforce Bullish Views Despite Projected Revenue Decline
summary: Cboe Global Markets (CBOE) reported that earnings have grown at an average rate of 19.2% per year over the last five years, with the latest year’s EPS growth at 26%, outpacing this long-term trend. Net profit margins reached 21.2%, up from 19.6% a year ago, even as revenue is forecast to decline by 17.1% annually for the next three years. With earnings still expected to rise by 6.1% per year and profitability showing resilience, investors face a nuanced picture. Recent margin gains provide...
